        "content": "<p>Is there a function like <code>mapForallTelescope</code> but for lambda with a bounded number of arguments's? Specifically I want to modify the body of a nested lambda expression, e.g.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>to</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y'</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>via some function that transforms <code>y</code> into <code>y'</code>.</p>",
        "id": 506605807,
